results.name: Number of degree-n irreducible polynomials over GF(4) with trace 1 and subtrace 0.
comment: Let a = RootOf( x^2+x+1 ) and b = 1+a. Same as number of degree-n irreducible polynomials over GF(4) with trace a and subtrace 0. Same as number of degree-n irreducible polynomials over GF(4) with trace b and subtrace 0.
link: E. N. Kuz'min, Irreducible polynomials over a finite field and an analogue of Gauss sums over a field of characteristic 2, Siberian Mathematical Journal, 32, 982-989 (1991).
Frank Ruskey, Number of irreducible polynomials over GF(4) with given trace and subtrace
mathematica: h[n_, 1, a_] := 1/n Sum[MoebiusMu[d] ddp[Mod[a+(d-1)/2, 2], n/d], {d, Select[Divisors[n], OddQ]}];
results.author: _Frank Ruskey_ and Nate Kube, Aug 26 2002
